      "question": "In $\\triangle ABC$, point $D$ lies on side $BC$ such that $\\angle ADC = \\angle BAC$. If $AC = 6$ cm and $BC = 9$ cm, find the length of $CD$.",
      "answer": "$4$ cm",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Consider $\\triangle ABC$ and $\\triangle DAC$. Given $\\angle ADC = \\angle BAC$ and $\\angle C$ is common to both triangles.",
          "By $AA$ similarity criterion, $\\triangle ABC \\sim \\triangle DAC$.",
          "Since the triangles are similar, the ratios of their corresponding sides are equal: $\\frac{AC}{DC} = \\frac{BC}{AC}$.",
          "Substitute the given values: $\\frac{6}{DC} = \\frac{9}{6}$, which simplifies to $DC = \\frac{36}{9} = 4$ cm."
        ],
        "derivation": "$In \\ \\triangle ABC \\ and \\ \\triangle DAC, \\angle ADC = \\angle BAC \\ (Given) \\ \\angle C = \\angle C \\ (Common) \\ \\therefore \\triangle ABC \\sim \\triangle DAC \\ (AA \\ similarity) \\ \\Rightarrow \\frac{AC}{DC} = \\frac{BC}{AC} \\ \\Rightarrow \\frac{6}{DC} = \\frac{9}{6} \\ \\Rightarrow 9 \\times DC = 36 \\ \\Rightarrow DC = 4 \\ cm$"
      },
